	abstract = {We present a detailed characterization of the Kepler-411 system (KOI 1781). This system was previously known to host two transiting planets: one with a period of 3 days (R = 2.4 R{\textless}SUB{\textgreater}⊕{\textless}/SUB{\textgreater}; Kepler-411b) and one with a period of 7.8 days (R = 4.4 R{\textless}SUB{\textgreater}⊕{\textless}/SUB{\textgreater}; Kepler-411c), as well as a transiting planetary candidate with a 58-day period (R = 3.3 R{\textless}SUB{\textgreater}⊕{\textless}/SUB{\textgreater}; KOI 1781.03) from Kepler photometry. Here, we combine Kepler photometry data and new transit timing variation (TTV) measurements from all the Kepler quarters with previous adaptive-optics imaging results, and dynamical simulations, in order to constrain the properties of the Kepler-411 system. From our analysis, we obtain masses of 25.6 ± 2.6 M{\textless}SUB{\textgreater}⊕{\textless}/SUB{\textgreater} for Kepler-411b and 26.4 ± 5.9 M{\textless}SUB{\textgreater}⊕{\textless}/SUB{\textgreater} for Kepler-411c, and we confirm the planetary nature of KOI 1781.03 with a mass of 15.2 ± 5.1 M{\textless}SUB{\textgreater}⊕{\textless}/SUB{\textgreater}, hence the name Kepler-411d. Furthermore, by assuming near-coplanarity of the system (mutual inclination below 30°), we discover a nontransiting planet, Kepler-411e, with a mass of 10.8 ± 1.1 M{\textless}SUB{\textgreater}⊕{\textless}/SUB{\textgreater} on a 31.5-day orbit, which has a strong dynamical interaction with Kepler-411d. With densities of 1.71 ± 0.39 g cm{\textless}SUP{\textgreater}-3{\textless}/SUP{\textgreater} and 2.32 ± 0.83 g cm{\textless}SUP{\textgreater}-3{\textless}/SUP{\textgreater}, both Kepler-411c and Kepler-411d belong to the group of planets with a massive core and a significant fraction of volatiles. Although Kepler-411b has a sub-Neptune size, it belongs to the group of rocky planets. {\textless}P /{\textgreater}Tables 2-4 are only available at the CDS via anonymous ftp to {\textless}A href="http://cdsarc.u-strasbg.fr"{\textgreater}http://cdsarc.u-strasbg.fr{\textless}/A{\textgreater} (ftp://130.79.128.5) or via {\textless}A href="http://cdsarc.u-strasbg.fr/viz-bin/qcat?J/A+A/624/A15"{\textgreater}http://cdsarc.u-strasbg.fr/viz-bin/qcat?J/A+A/624/A15{\textless}/A{\textgreater}},
	language = {en},
