extgreater}{\textless}sub{\textgreater}({\textless}i{\textgreater}f{\textless}i/{\textgreater}){\textless}sub/{\textgreater} = 108 days. The inner pair presents an orbital period ratio of 2.97, but a dynamical analysis of the system shows that it lays outside the 3:1 mean motion resonance. The planet GJ 163c, in particular, is a super-Earth with an equilibrium temperature of {\textless}i{\textgreater}T{\textless}i/{\textgreater}{\textless}sub{\textgreater}eq{\textless}sub/{\textgreater} = (302 ± 10)(1 − {\textless}i{\textgreater}A{\textless}i/{\textgreater}){\textless}sup{\textgreater}1/4{\textless}sup/{\textgreater} K and may lie in the so-called habitable zone for albedo values ({\textless}i{\textgreater}A{\textless}i/{\textgreater} = 0.34 − 0.89) moderately higher than that of Earth ({\textless}i{\textgreater}A{\textless}i/{\textgreater}{\textless}sub{\textgreater}⊕{\textless}sub/{\textgreater} = 0.2−0.3).},
